    en: "Catalytic converter theft is a persistent problem in New York. Thieves can cut a converter off a parked car in a few minutes. The 2022 amendments to Penal Law 165.54 made unlawful possession of a detached converter a crime, and General Business Law 399-ggg requires scrap metal dealers to record every converter purchase and hold it before processing. A theft victim should file a police report, which is the trigger for most auto insurance claims. Comprehensive auto insurance covers replacement minus the deductible; liability-only coverage does not."
